an nature. In the process, the contributors argue for the need to reject simplistic explanations and reinvent civil society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCivilization, Modern. 0aEthicszNetherlands. 0aEthics. 0aMoral conditions. 0aSocial ethics. 0aValues. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aBakker, Wieger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorgman, Erik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrink, Gabriël van den, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDekker, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHalman, Loek, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIngen, Erik van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLuijn, Heleen van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaalsté, Nicole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMare, Heidi de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWoets, Karen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 avan den Brink, Gabriël, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2016-2018z978311066731808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backlist 2015-2017z978311060644708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066278808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2015z97831110237620 cprintz978908964775740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048525706?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048525706423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/doc